The paper deals with the degrees of freedom (DoF) of a multi-hop MIMO broadcast network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of relays and delayed channel state information also suggests a possible connection to networking (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The communication aspect of the problem may also make it relevant to the communication sub-category (cs.COMM). Finally, the optimization of the network performance may involve mathematical analysis and algorithms, which could fall under the machine learning sub-category (cs.MA).
